    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup anchored by the high-upside profile of **Yordan Alvarez** (70.94) and **Junior Caminero** (70.65). **Yordan Alvarez** remains our premier offensive engine against Warren, where his elite xwOBA of 0.393 and favorable platoon advantage outweigh the slight park penalty. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** benefits from a strong SP skill matchup against Bradley, with his dynamic platoon advantage providing a significant boost to his base projection. While **Trea Turner** (68.42) and **Kyle Schwarber** (64.96) occupy the top tier, keep a close eye on **Caleb Durbin** (67.42); his high score is heavily driven by a massive 16% park factor adjustment and a favorable SP skill matchup, making him a sneaky play despite his lower slot in the order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s bench involved **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (50.22). While he possesses the sprint speed we prioritize to chase stolen bases, the combination of a difficult matchup against Sheehan and his status as a lineup-pending candidate pushed his efficiency score below our threshold for starting consideration. Conversely, **Dillon Dingler** (61.29) narrowly secured a start; his score was propped up by a rare confluence of a favorable park, a weak pitcher, and a slow delivery from Abbott, which creates a prime environment for **Dillon Dingler** to exploit on the basepaths. We continue to monitor **Hyeseong Kim** (57.49) closely, as his status remains lineup-pending; should he be removed from the batting order, expect the team to pivot toward players with higher guaranteed utility to preserve our game caps.",
